HEADWORD: Trillium
<hw>Tril"li*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.; cf. L.
<ets>trilix</ets> triple-woven, triple.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of liliaceous plants; the three-leaved nightshade; -- so called
because all the parts of the plant are in threes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

